{
  "stem": "8.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Now, my brother, the last two years also, started to learn a trade, because we thought that maybe he could help out in the family earning something, some way of to making a living.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "My younger brother couldn't do anything at that time.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "He was just a little boy.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, you know Hungary was not occupied by the Nazis, by the Germans, until 1944.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "March 19, 1944.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that was because the Regent of Hungary, whose name was Horthy, he collaborated with the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And, it became, really, a Nazi-inclined government and with our own Nazi Fascist party, which was called the Arrow Cross party, and they were-- they often attacked the Jews without any reason.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Of course, by this time, the Jews could not attend any schools.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Certain businesses had to be closed, even before the Germans came in.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So that the Hungarians themselves, they, they had regulations and laws that prevented the normal life of the Jews.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But, we were still free to travel and to talk to people anywhere.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The first day was-- the first day was March 19, 1944, when the German Army marched into Hungary.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In spite of their negotiations, they decided to occupy and Eichmann arrived to Budapest.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I was 15 and I wasn't really that much into politics or understanding what was going on.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So most of my experiences come from a perspective of a 15-year-old and 16-year-old, later.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When they came in, we were terrified.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And, my brother was a young man who loved football, or soccer, at that time it was called.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And, he traveled to Budapest regularly to see the soccer games.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
